      "content": "i see. so you're saying the humanitarian aspect doesn't really count as a \"win\" in geopolitics. but isn't that a bit of a narrow view? if an intervention prevents a genocide, isn't that a massive success for the international rules-based order, which is itself a core geopolitical goal? it feels like you're dismissing the \"humanitarian\" side as if it's less \"real\" than power dynamics.",
